Now you can use Alexa to control all your Smarthome devices! You can turn on/off your smartLock simply by giving orders to Alexa. 

First, select the "Enable Skills" button to link your elinkSmart account and find your lock. Find out more about connecting smart home devices to Alexa on Connected Smart Home Devices: http://amzn.to/291lR7u

To use this skill, you must first create a name for the lock device in the eSmartLock application. Once you know the device name, you can issue the following command to Alexa:
"Alexa, unlock the front door lock";
"Alexa, unlock living room lock";
"Alexa, unlock the kitchen lock";
"Alexa, unlock balcony lock";
